If you can switch the D to make Directed Autonomous Organisations you =
have me.

=20

I see the modern organisation being run by a small group of leaders =
using technology to shape the actions of varyingly autonomous actors =
=E2=80=93 they will have a bench of actors that are contracted to the =
company for years as a basic resource and they will sub in more =
autonomous actors as required on a task and cultural basis.

=20

I was thinking about my Spanish debt collection business the other day =
in this light =E2=80=93 it is run by 4 managers, then has 110 employees =
on a very flat structure that get allocated tasks (ie which debt to work =
on and which strategy to use, largely automatically). We then also use =
another 80 debt collectors employed by other agencies on a task basis =
=E2=80=93 ie we give them debts and we ask them to enact a given =
strategy . So essentially you have a management layer giving direction, =
computers breaking this direction down into tasks and assigning those =
tasks to the best available human and the human undertaking the task =
that the computer cannot do (call the debtor and negotiate, navigate the =
still analogue Spanish legal system). As we improve the tech and the =
Spanish legal system automates the middle will just get increasingly =
automated.=20

=20

Think you will always need a human at the helm because of the complexity =
and nuanced nature of the decision making required.

=20

Have added Aaron Dighon=E2=80=99s book to my audible list =E2=80=93 just =
need to finish =E2=80=9CTrade Wars are Class Wars=E2=80=9D first!

=20

